<TITLE> Devotees poised for tearful farewell to Durga </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com) Durga Puja, the greatest religious festival of the Hindu community, ends Sunday with the immersion of the idol of the goddess Durga bringing an end to the five-day celebration. Devotees are poised to bid the goddess a tearful goodbye while inviting her to return to them the next year. The religious chants on Bijoya Dashami, as the final day of the festival is called, starts at 7:30 Sunday morning. The Bijoya processions that will carry statues of the goddess for immersion will begin in the afternoon. According to the Bangladesh Puja Celebration Council, the Bijoya processions and immersions will take place between 2pm and 9pm. Women devotees will groom Durga with flowers and ornaments before the immersion ceremony. They will also groom themselves and festivities will end with the exchange of greetings. Sunday is a public holiday marking the occasion. President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed will greet members of the Hindu community on the day. State-run and private television channels and radios will air special programmes on the day while newspapers will publish special supplements on the great religious festival. bdnews
